  "prompt": "Does money laundering fall under criminal legislation?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is considered a serious criminal offense under both national and international law. Most countries have specific criminal legislation that addresses money laundering, typically including:\n\n1. Legal definitions of money laundering\n2. Criminal penalties and prosecution\n3. Mandatory reporting requirements for financial institutions\n4. Mechanisms for investigating and preventing money laundering activities\n\nIn many jurisdictions, money laundering is treated as a criminal offense that can result in substantial fines and imprisonment. The specific legal framework and penalties vary by country, but generally involve prosecuting individuals or organizations that attempt to conceal the origins of illegally obtained money.",
